
                              rwall.c
              <a small window to select your wallpaper>

features:
• visual gtk window for selecting your wall
• cache suport for more speedy opening

see ./makefile for a easy installation


§ installation

git clone https://github.com/getjared/rwall.git
cd rwall
make
sudo make install


§ dependencies

• c compiler (gcc or clang)
• make
• json-glib
• libsoup


§ quick-start

run it in the background through your .xinitrc
  • rwall --n &

once setup, you can create a keybind in something sxhkd
  # rwall
  super + w
  	rwall

there are 3 different options
• rwall --r (rounded corners)
• rwall --t (transparency)
• rwall --b (grab random wall from wallhaven)

key bindings:
q : quit the window
